2. Failure-Mode Overlay on the Phase Diagram
Layering this over your axes/phases: failures are "leakage vectors" that pull the system left/down. Each phase has dominant modes, with rituals as countermeasures. Visualize red arrows dragging toward low CQ/NTB, green shields pushing up/right.
Overlay Key:
Phase I (Extraction/Burnout): Dominant failures = High recognition latency (contributions ignored â†’ shame spirals), gatekeeping validation (knowledge hoarded â†’ calcification), resource depletion (use without regeneration â†’ backlog). Arrows: Steep downward from (low CQ, -0.4) to origin. Shield: Basic "Recognition Pulse" ritual to bootstrap out.
Phase II (Obligation Loop): Failures = Delayed validation (social guilt builds), optional rest (seasonal burnout), conditional resources (participation feels transactional). Arrows: Looping cycles around (mid CQ, -0.2)â€”stuck attractor. Shield: "Sabbath of the Commons" + "Mirroring Scribing" to break the loop.
Phase III (Resonant Circulation): Failures = Subtle ambiguities in knowledge (thickens over time), uneven rest enforcement (pockets of drain), minor waste (slow NTB erosion). Arrows: Shallow leftward drifts from (high CQ, +0.1). Shield: "Pancake Report" + "Simplification Push" for fine-tuning.
Phase IV (Abundance Engine): Rare failures = Gaming (anti-damping needed), over-simplification (wisdom dilutes), unlock friction (resources bottleneck). Arrows: Rare downward blips, but self-correcting via resonance. Shield: "Sovereignty Shield" + "Regeneration Feedback" to maintain hum.
